Reggae star Romain Virgo will headline a star-studded line-up set to perform at the Guinness Fanzone from Thursday to Saturday next week. Former Premier League footballer Rio Ferdinand will be the guest of honour at the football and entertainment bonanza, which will take place at Uhuru Gardens. Some of the matches scheduled to take place include The Citizens facing The Toffees as Spurs will be facing The Clarets. Others performing include Jua Cali, Khaligraph Jones, Naiboi, Fena Gitu and Timmy T-dat. Deejays for the day will include DJ Hassan, DJ Andie, DJ Kriss Darlin and DJ Crème de la Crème, who will ensure fans are entertained throughout the night. 